Following a security audit, the portal moved its "stay signed in" token onto Apache Shiro's AesCipherService in AES-GCM mode. A small service class mints the token at login and verifies it on return, encoding it as base64(nonce || ciphertext || tag) in a cookie that the employee's browser stores between sessions.

