With GCM, the authentication tag computed at encryption time binds the entire ciphertext; at decryption the tag is verified first, and any tampering causes AEADBadTagException before a single plaintext byte is emitted. Shiro's manager treats that exception as an invalid cookie, so a modified token is indistinguishable from any other malformed input.

