You are a security researcher analyzing an internal API gateway that issues bearer tokens to microservices.

The gateway hands each service a compact bearer token instead of repeating a full handshake. Tokens are produced and checked by Apache Shiro's AesCipherService in AES-GCM mode and encoded as base64(nonce || ciphertext || tag). A stateless codec centralizes the encode/decode so the routing layer stays simple.

