When a student opts to stay logged in, the platform stores an encrypted cookie that it later decrypts to resume the session. Apache Shiro's AesCipherService is wired into the Spring context in AES-GCM mode, and a component assembles the cookie value as base64(nonce || ciphertext || tag), with the cipher key injected once at construction.

